solution.p:
  We see that x is the length of the shortest side in \triangle ABE. We know the short side in \triangle FCE and the lengths of the medium sides in each triangle.  If we form the ratios of the short sides and the medium sides, we obtain the following proportion.

\dfrac{\text{larger triangle}}{\text{smaller triangle}}:~~~~~\dfrac{x}{4}~~~=~~~\dfrac{15}{6}

To solve the proportion, we cross-multiply to get

image.latex-image:

